
<div id="header" class="section" data-type="background">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-md-12">
			<h1 class="text-center"><strong>Vigilant</strong></h1>
			<p class=" text-center">A crowdsource app for tracking problems in a city</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<div id="motivation" class="section" data-type="background">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-md-6 sectionDescriptionCanvas">
			<div class="sectionTitleCanvas">
				<h1>Motivation</h1>
				<h2>What leads our goal</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="sectionTextCanvas">
				<p class="text-left lead">Many cities around the World face some problems every year: holes on the streets, sliding, flooding and structural problems are some well‚Äêknown examples. Unfortunately many of them take a long time to be solved because of the bureaucracies or depend on the media (TV, News, Radio and Internet) to be known by the government while many citizens have to face this scenario day by day.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="col-md-6 contentSectionCanvas">
			<%= image_tag("motivation-city.png") %>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<div id="statistics" class="section">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-md-4 sectionDescriptionCanvas">
			<div class="sectionTitleCanvas">
				<h1>Statistics</h1>
				<h2>What supports our idea</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="sectionTextCanvas">
				<p class="text-left lead">In order to validate and understand the social problems we created an online form and it was sent to friends and known people.
				</p>
				<p class="text-left lead">After a while it was collected 114 responses from more than 25 cities in Brazil. Despite the form was responded only by brazilian, the results turned out to be surprisingly interesting.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="col-md-8 sectionDataVisCanvas">
			<div class="sectionDataVisWrapper">
				<div class="graphicDataCanvas">
					<div class="plotTitleCanvas">
						<h1 class="">Are you satisfied with your city?</h1>
					</div>
					<div class="plotCanvas">
						<p class="text-center"><%= image_tag("gf-satisfaction.png") %></p>

					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="textDataCanvas">
					<div class="dataConclusionCanvas">
						<h2>92% have some level of dissatisfaction with the city they live </h2>
					</div>
					<div class="graphLegendCanvas">
						<h2>Legend</h2>
						<ul>
							<li><div class="legend legend-1"></div>Very Satisfied (4%)</li>
							<li><div class="legend legend-2"></div> Satisfied (4%)</li>
							<li><div class="legend legend-3"></div>Partially Satisfied (29%)</li>
							<li><div class="legend legend-4"></div>Not Satisfied (31)%</li>
							<li><div class="legend legend-5"></div>Very Unsatisfied (31%)</li>

						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="clear"></div>
			</div>
			<div class="sectionDataVisWrapper">
				<div class="graphicDataCanvas">
					<div class="plotTitleCanvas">
						<h1 class="">When you find a problem in your city, do you usually report it to city hall? </h1>
					</div>
					<div class="plotCanvas">
						<p class="text-center"><%= image_tag("gf-report.png") %></p>
						
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="textDataCanvas">
					<div class="dataConclusionCanvas">
						<h2>Just 14% complain formally to the city hall</h2>
					</div>
					<div class="graphLegendCanvas">
						<h2>Legend</h2>
						<ul>
							<li><div class="legend legend-3"></div>Partially Satisfied (14%)</li>
							<li><div class="legend legend-4"></div>Not Satisfied (86%)</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="clear"></div>
			</div>
			
			

		</div>
	</div>
</div>

